<p>I'm trying to fix the height of a div inside a section to 100px. However, no matter what I try, the height reverts back to 'auto' and re-sizes depending on the amount of content in the div. </p>  <p>Here's the HTML code:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;section id="social" class="tab-content active"&gt;     &lt;div id = "socialDiv"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/section&gt; </code></pre>  <p>and here's what I've tried so far</p>  <p>CSS: </p>  <pre><code>social{height:100px; line-height:20px;overflow:hidden;} .socialDiv{height:100px !important; line-height:20px;overflow:hidden;} </code></pre>  <p>jQuery: </p>  <pre><code>$('.socialDiv').css({'height':100+'px'}); $('.socialDiv').height( 100 ); </code></pre>  <p>Unfortunately none of these work. I'd appreciate any and all help on this.</p>  <p>PS. I don't know if this will matter or not, but this is part of a Chrome extension and this section is part of a popup window that displays during execution.  </p>